            "function": {
              "arguments": "{\"file_text\":\"## Manual Review Escalation Workflow\\n\\nThis document describes the manual review escalation feature for the Loan Workbench platform.\\n\\n### Overview\\n\\nThe manual review escalation workflow enables loan applications to be escalated from underwriters or analyst-managers to compliance reviewers for additional scrutiny and approval. This is particularly important for high-risk applications, applications exceeding approval thresholds, or applications subject to regulatory requirements.\\n\\n### Workflow States\\n\\nEscalations move through the following states:\\n\\n- **pending** — Escalation created, awaiting compliance reviewer action\\n- **approved** — Reviewer approved the escalation; application can proceed\\n- **rejected** — Reviewer identified issues; application cannot proceed without resolution\\n- **completed** — Escalation resolution is finalized and documented\\n\\n### Integration with State Transitions\\n\\nThe escalation system integrates with the loan application state machine:\\n\\n1. Applications move through states: `intake` → `review` → `underwriting` → `decision` → `finalized`\\n2. When transitioning `underwriting` → `decision`, a `manual-review-escalation` notification event is mandatory\\n3. This event can trigger an escalation workflow if configured\\n\\n### Database Schema\\n\\n```sql\\nCREATE TABLE manual_review_escalations (\\n    id                TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\\n    application_id    TEXT NOT NULL REFERENCES loan_applications(id),\\n    escalated_by      TEXT NOT NULL REFERENCES users(id),\\n    assigned_reviewer TEXT NOT NULL REFERENCES users(id),\\n    status            TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'pending',\\n    reason            TEXT NOT NULL,\\n    resolution_notes  TEXT,\\n    created_at        TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT (datetime('now')),\\n    resolved_at       TEXT\\n);\\n```\\n\\n### API Endpoints\\n\\n#### 1. Initiate Escalation\\n\\n**POST /api/escalations**\\n\\nInitiates a manual review escalation for a loan application.\\n\\n**Request:**\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"applicationId\\\": \\\"app-2\\\",\\n  \\\"assignedReviewerId\\\": \\\"u-3\\\",\\n  \\\"reason\\\": \\\"High loan amount exceeds underwriter authority; requires compliance review.\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Authorized Roles:** `analyst-manager`, `compliance-reviewer`\\n\\n**Response:** 201 Created\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"id\\\": \\\"esc-abc123\\\",\\n  \\\"applicationId\\\": \\\"app-2\\\",\\n  \\\"escalatedBy\\\": \\\"u-2\\\",\\n  \\\"assignedReviewer\\\": \\\"u-3\\\",\\n  \\\"status\\\": \\\"pending\\\",\\n  \\\"reason\\\": \\\"High loan amount exceeds underwriter authority; requires compliance review.\\\",\\n  \\\"resolutionNotes\\\": null,\\n  \\\"createdAt\\\": \\\"2025-01-15T10:30:00Z\\\",\\n  \\\"resolvedAt\\\": null\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Errors:**\\n- `400 Bad Request` — Missing or invalid fields\\n- `403 Forbidden` — Insufficient role or delegated session\\n- `404 Not Found` — Application not found\\n\\n#### 2. Resolve Escalation\\n\\n**PATCH /api/escalations/:id/resolve**\\n\\nUpdates the status of a pending escalation with reviewer decision.\\n\\n**Request:**\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"status\\\": \\\"approved\\\",\\n  \\\"resolutionNotes\\\": \\\"All compliance requirements satisfied. Application may proceed to decision.\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Authorized Roles:** `compliance-reviewer` (only assigned reviewer)\\n\\n**Query Parameters:**\\n- `status` (required): `approved` | `rejected` | `completed`\\n- `resolutionNotes` (optional): Details explaining the decision\\n\\n**Response:** 200 OK\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"id\\\": \\\"esc-abc123\\\",\\n  \\\"applicationId\\\": \\\"app-2\\\",\\n  \\\"escalatedBy\\\": \\\"u-2\\\",\\n  \\\"assignedReviewer\\\": \\\"u-3\\\",\\n  \\\"status\\\": \\\"approved\\\",\\n  \\\"reason\\\": \\\"High loan amount exceeds underwriter authority; requires compliance review.\\\",\\n  \\\"resolutionNotes\\\": \\\"All compliance requirements satisfied. Application may proceed to decision.\\\",\\n  \\\"createdAt\\\": \\\"2025-01-15T10:30:00Z\\\",\\n  \\\"resolvedAt\\\": \\\"2025-01-15T11:45:00Z\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Errors:**\\n- `403 Forbidden` — Non-compliance-reviewer or not assigned to escalation\\n- `404 Not Found` — Escalation not found\\n- `409 Conflict` — Escalation already resolved\\n\\n#### 3. Get Application Escalations\\n\\n**GET /api/escalations/:applicationId**\\n\\nRetrieves all escalations (past and present) for a loan application.\\n\\n**Authorized Roles:** `underwriter`, `analyst-manager`, `compliance-reviewer`\\n\\n**Response:** 200 OK\\n```json\\n[\\n  {\\n    \\\"id\\\": \\\"esc-abc123\\\",\\n    \\\"applicationId\\\": \\\"app-2\\\",\\n    \\\"escalatedBy\\\": \\\"u-2\\\",\\n    \\\"assignedReviewer\\\": \\\"u-3\\\",\\n    \\\"status\\\": \\\"pending\\\",\\n    \\\"reason\\\": \\\"High loan amount exceeds underwriter authority; requires compliance review.\\\",\\n    \\\"resolutionNotes\\\": null,\\n    \\\"createdAt\\\": \\\"2025-01-15T10:30:00Z\\\",\\n    \\\"resolvedAt\\\": null\\n  }\\n]\\n```\\n\\n#### 4. Get Reviewer Escalations\\n\\n**GET /api/escalations/reviewer/:reviewerId**\\n\\nRetrieves all escalations assigned to a specific compliance reviewer.\\n\\n**Authorized Roles:** `compliance-reviewer`\\n\\n**Query Parameters:**\\n- `status` (optional): Filter by status (`pending` | `approved` | `rejected` | `completed`)\\n\\n**Response:** 200 OK\\n```json\\n[\\n  {\\n    \\\"id\\\": \\\"esc-abc123\\\",\\n    \\\"applicationId\\\": \\\"app-2\\\",\\n    \\\"escalatedBy\\\": \\\"u-2\\\",\\n    \\\"assignedReviewer\\\": \\\"u-3\\\",\\n    \\\"status\\\": \\\"pending\\\",\\n    \\\"reason\\\": \\\"High loan amount exceeds underwriter authority; requires compliance review.\\\",\\n    \\\"resolutionNotes\\\": null,\\n    \\\"createdAt\\\": \\\"2025-01-15T10:30:00Z\\\",\\n    \\\"resolvedAt\\\": null\\n  }\\n]\\n```\\n\\n#### 5. Get Escalation Details\\n\\n**GET /api/escalations/details/:id**\\n\\nRetrieves details for a specific escalation.\\n\\n**Authorized Roles:** `analyst-manager`, `compliance-reviewer`\\n\\n**Response:** 200 OK\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"id\\\": \\\"esc-abc123\\\",\\n  \\\"applicationId\\\": \\\"app-2\\\",\\n  \\\"escalatedBy\\\": \\\"u-2\\\",\\n  \\\"assignedReviewer\\\": \\\"u-3\\\",\\n  \\\"status\\\": \\\"pending\\\",\\n  \\\"reason\\\": \\\"High loan amount exceeds underwriter authority; requires compliance review.\\\",\\n  \\\"resolutionNotes\\\": null,\\n  \\\"createdAt\\\": \\\"2025-01-15T10:30:00Z\\\",\\n  \\\"resolvedAt\\\": null\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### Authorization & Security\\n\\n- **Creation:** Only `analyst-manager` and `compliance-reviewer` roles can escalate\\n- **Resolution:** Only the assigned `compliance-reviewer` can resolve escalations\\n- **Delegated Sessions:** Cannot initiate or resolve escalations (security barrier)\\n- **Read Access:** All roles can view escalations for applications they have access to\\n\\n### Audit Trail\\n\\nAll escalation activities are logged via the audit service:\\n\\n- `escalation.initiated` — Created when escalation is initiated\\n- `escalation.resolved` — Created when escalation is resolved with decision\\n\\nAudit entries capture:\\n- Actor (who initiated/resolved)\\n- Previous and new escalation states\\n- Timestamp\\n- Source service\\n\\n### Business Rules\\n\\n1. **Authority Thresholds:**\\n   - Underwriters can approve loans up to $1M\\n   - Analyst-managers can approve loans up to $2.5M\\n   - Loans exceeding $2.5M must be escalated to compliance reviewers\\n\\n2. **California Loans:**\\n   - California loans (loanState=\\\"CA\\\") between $50K–$5M may require escalation\\n   - Subject to `californiaRules` feature flag\\n\\n3. **State Transitions:**\\n   - Applications can only be escalated before reaching \\\"finalized\\\" state\\n   - Escalation is optional but recommended during underwriting→decision transition\\n\\n### Error Handling\\n\\n**Common Errors:**\\n\\n```\\nFORBIDDEN: Delegated sessions cannot initiate escalations.\\nFORBIDDEN: Role 'underwriter' cannot escalate applications.\\nFORBIDDEN: Only compliance-reviewers can resolve escalations.\\nNOT_FOUND: Application 'app-invalid' not found.\\nNOT_FOUND: Escalation 'esc-invalid' not found.\\nINVALID_STATE: Escalation is already 'approved'. Only pending escalations can be resolved.\\n```\\n\\n### Testing\\n\\nIntegration tests verify:\\n- Escalation creation with valid/invalid data\\n- Role-based authorization\\n- Delegated session restrictions\\n- Escalation resolution workflows\\n- Status transitions and terminal states\\n- Audit trail generation\\n- Application filtering and retrieval\\n\\nRun tests:\\n```bash\\nnpm run test -- escalations.test.ts\\n```\\n\\n### Examples\\n\\n#### Example 1: Escalate a High-Amount Loan\\n\\n```bash\\ncurl -X POST http://localhost:3000/api/escalations \\\\\\n  -H \\\"Content-Type: application/json\\\" \\\\\\n  -H \\\"Authorization: ******" \\\\\\n  -d '{\\n    \\\"applicationId\\\": \\\"app-3\\\",\\n    \\\"assignedReviewerId\\\": \\\"u-3\\\",\\n    \\\"reason\\\": \\\"Loan amount $2M exceeds analyst-manager threshold; compliance review required per policy.\\\"\\n  }'\\n```\\n\\n#### Example 2: Compliance Reviewer Approves Escalation\\n\\n```bash\\ncurl -X PATCH http://localhost:3000/api/escalations/esc-abc123/resolve \\\\\\n  -H \\\"Content-Type: application/json\\\" \\\\\\n  -H \\\"Authorization: ******" \\\\\\n  -d '{\\n    \\\"status\\\": \\\"approved\\\",\\n    \\\"resolutionNotes\\\": \\\"Applicant meets all CA regulatory requirements. Income verified. Collateral appraisal complete. Approved for final decision.\\\"\\n  }'\\n```\\n\\n#### Example 3: Retrieve All Pending Escalations for a Reviewer\\n\\n```bash\\ncurl \\\"http://localhost:3000/api/escalations/reviewer/u-3?status=pending\\\" \\\\\\n  -H \\\"Authorization: ******"\\n```\\n\",\"path\":\"Y:\\\\.sources\\\\localm-tuts\\\\courses\\\\_examples\\\\ctx-sdlc\\\\lessons\\\\01-why-context-engineering\\\\without-context\\\\src\\\\backend\\\\ESCALATION_WORKFLOW.md\"}",
